[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating factory use**\n\nI'm considering the use of the factory in the `Convert.toJavaObject` method. If I'm only converting enums, it seems like the factory isn't needed at all. However, it does create a REFIID, but I'm finding that it's not operating within an OS context. This might suggest that the implementation could be cleaner or more streamlined. I'll explore further to confirm if simplifying this part might be beneficial.\n\n**Considering reflection in tests**\n\nI’m pondering whether using reflection in tests is unfeasible. It seems like CallbackProxy could handle half of it. For direct conversion via `Class.forName(\"...Convert\").getDeclaredMethod(\"toVariant\", Object.class)`, it does appear possible. However, it depends on whether the public API needs it due to the Convert class being package-private. I’d really prefer to avoid this approach if possible, just to keep things cleaner.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07a962d7273acd390169f2d814353481a093e2fc1fa24c420d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8tgonf0jnaD3ieT8T-gAcLPZu3KQchKI5lN5eytW5gAkwNGU45uGpjcUuPL7M7IRq1T0Mj_l5MK2BxbxGrfZ3uT8YzaURy4zcV4TtTCgE5d2ie4KhtKjLjK0xClcxyAWSU3VGUAWoimFmZ03SBwAjCKWuJJV0WsCbVdhI56BtyDdGpv2C889LJv_8Son2Sdu5S9RpWqVXDXehcNxpHLhHKb9_Fa_dxrEIIBIkZZSouiWQOW99_DQg5gAfp9lNF6yHjhGTgnfUhm5J8s8FFPYTRJeIh2nvwtHIzzGKbQhK99DmcigBesLiSl-AUTV7Sv89zHIEOrSLLpQRMFUNSM06REt61ghEF5NTX2SoT8pteYm5d20bRIV0MxuM0TMse6hpqo0Nxpl0mdOL8r3994j2aisdF1Z9u48HXnvihSPnxdWi7mxGUO873LVKtyKL2dApruwxdIYCgFfkhdcg8s8j_LUfydr5wt6lqC7CqzRA6UcNNWDdCJs7BjfneH5LSfTj8FQY04OtGJM-QuZmApcgr-WfCGbnA6FiJLyOSqv28ppQZtxjN2JTeSG4g3n2z58vehCNUQDbwAucurqpgIftjCMwo8AetzIDxhuw6Zte7mkrFecsHjaOidJnOCtYfMZaDSCVT8693qGAhSArB9zKNjIlujpYDrQaW77rxCP6sU-LysJ6WecBbVk3sTsEjkN5wZNedkrNZekanjAeajfN6fDas4jlp06_TpakbAOOE4Tz1tg-D_ucIUhq7-i-bhPveqZajHV5E_fiBIlI5CfRpelPlaXpAbA8mLEjAoFxg--8L8UHA0qf9zGbToyIpI9xP